==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Revere
<hw>Re*vere"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Revered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Revering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>revereri</ets>; pref.
<ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>vereri</ets> to fear, perh. akin to E.
<ets>wary</ets>: cf. F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧v⟦eacute⟧rer</ets>.]</ety> <def>To
regard with reverence, or profound respect and affection, mingled with
awe or fear; to venerate; to reverence; to honor in
estimation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Marcus Aurelius, whom he rather <qex>revered</qex> as his father
than treated as his partner in the empire.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To venerate; adore; reverence.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reverence</ent>⟦br⟧
